                <note rend="inline" type="source">121.5493/11–849: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-08T20:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 8, 1949—8 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:35 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1941. ReDeptels 725, October 20, and 759, November 1,<note n="10"
                        xml:id="d1018fn10">For latter, see <ref target="#pg_1149">p.
                        1149</ref>.</note> next two telegrams Peiping No. series<note n="11"
                        xml:id="d1018fn11">Telegrams Nos. 1942 and 1943 printed <hi rend="italic"
                            >infra</hi> and <ref target="#pg_1151">p. 1151</ref>,
                        respectively.</note> give English texts notes addressed Chou En-lai on two
                    subjects, Assistant [<hi rend="italic">Am</hi>.] Military Attaché Soule exit
                    permit and American Government real property Tsingtao under respective dates
                    November 7 and 8, both dispatched today. Recommend no publicity for present.</p>
                <p>Department please inform Nanking, Tsingtao appropriately, also Tientsin at
                    discretion.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clubb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
